Neocon-progressive accusations that Trump is 'appeasing' Putin completely miss the point. 
Putin is relieved that MAGA won in America, wants to demonstrate that he can be a working international partner to a non-woke-progressivist US administration, and is therefore positioned now to deliver terms for a Russo-Ukraine peace deal incomparably more reasonable than anything that would have been plausible with the previous US government in power. It might even be good game theory for the Ukrainians to profess profound disappointment (thus giving the Russians more face for less gain), but it would be profoundly misguided to try to sabotage the process. Their bargaining position is only going to deteriorate from here. The EU is, of course, wholly irrelevant to any of this. ...

... The globalist progressives are resigned to a world order in which a firmly cemented Sino-Russian partnership is set against America (and its various special needs friends). The Trump administration is not resigned to this. This is absolutely crucial context.
It doesn't, and this means it has powerful incentives not to humiliate Trump Chamberlain-at-Munich style.
